Project 1: Hosting a Static Website on Ec2 (Beginner)
-----------------------------------------------------

Step 1 : Launch a Ec2 Instance 
_______
Configuration to choose: 
- AMI - Quick Start = Ubuntu
- Instance type     = t2.micro
- Key Pair          = Create or use existing
- Network           = Now default 
- Security Group    = Allow SSH - Your IP
                      Allow HTTP - Anywhere 
- Elastic Block Vol = Default 

Step 2 : Connect to the Ec2 Instance
_______
Either connect directly through the option provided by the Ec2 
                            or 
Connect through terminal using the command
>> ssh -i  filename.pem ubuntu@Ec2IPaddress

Step 3:  Configure the Nginx / Apache or Install the Web Server 
______
Here we will use the nginx because its simple and fast 

Run these commands on Ec2 : 
>> sudo apt update -y 
>> sudo apt install nginx -y
>> sudo systemctl  start nginx 
>> sudo systemctl enable nginx

To check on which port the  nginx is running use: 
>> sudo netstat -tulnp | grep  nginx

Now Open the browser and visit :
>> http://your - Ec2 - Public IP 

Step 4: Replace the default WebSite with Your Own 
_______
Remove the default nginx page: 
>> sudo rm /var/www/html/index.nginx-debian.html
Create your real website file
>> sudo vim /var/www/html/index.html

To add the CSS and JS files use  the following commands: 
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/css
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/js

Paste the HTML code in the html directory :

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First EC2 Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Hello from Amith's EC2 Website!</h1>
    <p>This website is hosted on an EC2 instance.</p>

    <button id="btn">Click Me</button>
    <p id="message"></p>

    <script src="js/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

Paste this in a "style.css" file in css directory 
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background: #f0f0f0;
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 60px;
}

h1 {
    color: #333;
}

button {
    padding: 12px 20px;
    font-size: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: #007bff;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
}

button:hover {
    background: #0056b3;
}

Paste this  in "script.js" in js directory 

document.getElementById("btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
    document.getElementById("message").textContent = "Button clicked! Welcome Amith ðŸš€";
});


Restart the nginx: >> sudo systemctl restart nginx
Test the nginx   : >> curl http://localhost



